20:
MAGIA FEST, Lord Alk! THAT is the
source of my vexations!
24:
My neurons are plagued by one
question: wherefore did you NOT
invite me?!
28:
Er... I didn't really think about it too
much. I didn't know you were into
stuff like that, for one.
34:
Of COURSE I am! Festivals, concerts...
Giant ROBOTS, Alk! Who better to
invite to such an occasion?!
38:
Huh... I just didn't think a ninja
samurai would be into school life
stuff, but I guess I was wrong.
42:
It wasn't all fun and games, though.
Some real crazy stuff went down
there too.
47:
It DID?! Now you're bragging
about—oh, why must you hit a poor
droid while he's down?!
51:
Oh the tragedy! The pain, the
loneliness! I feel myself slipping into
the darkness with every second...
56:
Geez, sorry! I really had no idea it
was that important to you!
60:
Well, whatever, it's done. Time to get
over it!
65:
Would you not allow me to GRIEVE
this tremendous loss?! Would you
deny me even that?
70:
All right, all right. Here, I'll make it up
to you. Come along with us!
85:
The SUN—its rays guide our way
forward!
The SEA—its waves beckon us on!
The SUMMER—its warm embrace
compels us...
TO REVEL!
92:
I, Zantetsu, the Ninja Samurai on the
Shore, have arrived to heed the
summer's call!
96:
...A fundoshi?! Is that supposed to be
a fundoshi?
100:
Indeed. A traditional loincloth
designed especially for me by one
of Dia's friends.
104:
Verily, the fundoshi is the traditional,
FUNdamental spirit of the ninja
samurai! What do you think?!
109:
Pretty sure traditional fundoshi don't
have a strobe light attached.
118:
Hahaha! Lady Stella's eyes are sharp
and wise as ever! She understands
the appeal!
122:
What's more, this new body frame is
also the stuff of heroes and legends!
125:
With this, I can unleash my full
potential on this seaside vacance!
Behold—
130:
Unprecedented mobility... Witness
my summer ninja skills:
Mizugumo Hover no Jutsu!!!
134:
Aren't ninjas supposed to be
stealthy? And NOT ride jet skis
around?
138: Yeah, well... At least he's having fun.
158:
Know you met your end to my
nautical ninja techniques, foul
beasts!
164:
Are you hurt, young one? Do not
fear, for I have vanquished thy foes!
168:
Justice reigns o'er the ocean waves
once again, and it was I—Zantetsu,
the ninja samurai—who has
restored order!
172: Um, thank you, Mr. Ninja Samurai...
175:
And with that, the matter is settled
most favorably.
178:
Sorry we're late! You really helped us
out by looking after that kid... We
can't thank you enough!
181:
Truly, it was nothing—we must all
thank fortune that an ally of justice
such as myself happened to be
present at the scene of the incident.
186:
We've had so many monster
incidents this year, we're struggling
to keep up. Just don't have the
manpower.
188:
We hired on assistants, but we're still
understaffed... If you don't mind,
would you be willing to help us out
going forward too?
191:
I see, I have understood the nature
of your predicament. If you would
have my aid, I would gladly proffer it.
195:
We will strive for PEACE in our time,
and on our shores!
206:
Deplorable—to beset these guiltless
sightseers... Unfortunately to you that
you had to learn the true power of
my Hyper Oscillating Blade!
210:
Pretty sure he's completely
forgotten we're even here.
215:
B-but it's okay, he's helping so many
people. I think it's wonderful what
he's doing.
220:
Heck yeah! I think I'm going to join
up with him tomorrow and help out!
223:
Hey, Mr. Ninja Samurai! When are
you off work? Wanna hang out with
us later?
230:
Yeah, good call, Yuna. I'm definitely
coming along next time!
235:
Ah, the adulation... the passionate
eyes all fixed on me... This is the very
manifestation of my desires...
245:
What the?! What's this all of a
sudden?
249:
NO! I've been a fool! An utter,
inexcusable BAKA!
253:
This empty craving for instant
gratification—for the attention of
others... It's wrong!
257: This isn't what it means to be a HERO!
261:
I mean, most people don't call
themselves that anyway. It's kinda
cringe.
265: What? I don't think it is!
270:
But I must aspire to that lofty
appellation! To the glorious heights
of nobility that come with the title
"Hero"!
274:
*sigh*
I fear I must take your leave...
I know not how long I will be away.
279:
Man, that was one sudden mood
swing.
282:
Do not search for me—for I wish not
to be found.
Farewell, my comrades.
286: Okay. Dinner's at 7 pm, by the way.
294:
That colorful personality's just a part
of his whole shtick, I guess.
299:
Oh, how long and arduous is the
path of a true hero...
